»CL9:                         c o m p e t i t i o n s


»CL0:    competitions  will be held during the whole party, first one begins in
saturday  after  midnight.   between  competitions  there will be a lot of
suprise  and  fast  compos  held,  but these will be kept in top secret to
avoid  possible preparations ;> the only thing we are going to tell you is
that  you  will  definitelly  need a computer for some of competitions [no
shit!   ;>]  and  even more, you'll need some old, used and trashed floppy
disks.

    voting  is  organized right after the final competitions end in sunday
afternoon.   voting  system  will be the same as on previous [ss3] party -
you  will  receive your personal voting sheet with possibility to vote for
best competitor in each category.  one vote counts as one point.

























»CL9:                           --- categories ---

»CL8:                            -- audio/visual --
»CL0:amiga 64k intro        [64k=65535 bytes - external data files not allowed]
pc 64k intro           [64k=65535 bytes - external data files not allowed]
amiga demo          [8mb = 8192k = 8388608 bytes - animations go to wild!]
pc demo             [8mb = 8192k = 8388608 bytes - animations go to wild!]
wild                               [VHS, AVI, MPEG, ANIM, COMPUTER, OTHER]

»CL8:                               -- audio --
»CL0:4channel modules                             [700k max - PROTRACKER ONLY!]
multichannel modules             [1mb max - XM,MOD,S3M,IT,SOUNDSTUDIO,DBM]

»CL8:                               -- visual --
»CL0:pixel art                                   [640x512x8 (256 colours) max!]
photoshop                                      [800x600x24 (24 bits) max!]
raytrace                                       [800x600x24 (24 bits) max!]
ascii                                              [80x24 characters max!]






















»CL9:                          --- compo machines ---

»CL0:amiga: 1. a1200 + blizzardppc 603e [060/50 + ppc603e/160] + 32mb fastmem
       2. a1200 + blizzard 1230 [030/50] + 16mb fastmem

»CL1:pc:    p2 celeron 333mmx + asus [riva128] vesa3.0
         GUS & SB clone installed in the same machine
          DOS7 [win98] [min 500k base memory]
































»CL9:                       --- competition details ---
        --- [for those always complaining about competitions] ---

»CL0:    since ss4 comes up with the new conception of competition schedule, in
order  to  free  up  sunday  afternoon's overload, there will be 3 [three]
deadlines.   graphics  categories  will  be  shown twice during the party.
more  info on these deadlines and competition time table could be found in
schedule   part   of   this  invitation.   almost  all  time  between  the
competitions  will  be  filled  up  with fast and suprise competitions, so
there is almost no chance to get bored during whole party time.  ;>>

    amiga  and  pc  categories  will not be mixed in any way.  if there is
only   one   entry   for  the  specific  demo  or  intro  competition,  it
automatically wins the competition and gets the prize [if planned for that
competition].   music  categories  are  expelled from this rule, all music
competes  together  in the appropriate category [4channel or multichannel]
nevertheless it is made on amiga or pc.























»CL0:    music  categories,  in  which  normally  we get too many entries, will
probably  be  preselected, most likely leaving 10 modules in each category
to  compete.   that situation will provide better listening to competiting
tunes  and a chance to actually listen multichannel music without becoming
dead  bored.   the  jury will be spontaneusly selected at the party place,
and  it  will  most  likely  consist  of musicians from all present active
groups.

    4channel  competition is protracker only, which means that all modules
must  be  playable from classic protracker 2.3.  module can be made on pc,
but  must  be playable by pt2.3 on amiga.  this competition will be played
from  amiga,  using  hippoplayer.   amiga  &  pc  entries  are mixed, this
category is multiplatform.

    multichannel  pc  entry  can  be  made  in fasttracker[_ii] (xm, mod),
impulsetracker (it), or screamtracker (s3m) format.  pc multichannels will
be played from modplug [or some better player, if available].























»CL0:    multichannel  amiga  entry  can  be  made  in  soundstudio  [mmd3]  or
digibooster  [dbm]  format.   amiga  multichannels  will  be  played  from
hippoplayer.    amiga   &   pc   entries   are  mixed,  this  category  is
multiplatform.

    graphics  competition  entries  will  be  displayed  from  appropriate
machines,  depending on their resolution and depth, but author can ask for
specific  machine  to  be  used  to  show  his  work.  same goes for ascii
competition, ansi is not allowed!

    we suggest you bring your wild entry on vhs tape.  alternativelly, you
may  use  some  od  the  compo machines as animation player in some of the
common  formats  on amiga or pc.  if your production utilises some special
software  or  hardware or whatever you use, you must bring it with you but
you must inform us before party starts [before april 3th!].

























